President Biden has announced his intent to appoint several individuals as members of the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. The board is responsible for guiding the center's mission, which includes serving as a memorial to President Kennedy, presenting world-class performing arts, and leading national performing arts education policy and programs. The appointed individuals include David C. Bohnett, a philanthropist and technology entrepreneur; Tatiana Copeland, co-owner and president of Bouchaine Vineyards; Robert Drury Lenhard, a partner at Covington & Burling, LLP; Phefelia Nez, the First Lady of the Navajo Nation; David Mark Rubenstein, co-founder and co-chairman of The Carlyle Group; Cari B. Sacks, an active philanthropist; and Hilda L. Solis, Los Angeles County Supervisor for the First District. Each member brings unique experiences and expertise to the board.